{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsSB4AqWYpXk1nRtf3u7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Root cause and fix:\n\n- **Root cause**: The `es-config` ConfigMap had `node.name:` set to a blank value (invalid — ES requires a non-null value) and `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed at the wrong namespace (`.default.svc` instead of `.elasticsearch.svc`). Because it's mounted via `subPath`, already-running pods (`es-cluster-0/1`) kept their original good copy in memory, but `es-cluster-2`'s PVC and pod had been wiped and recreated, so it mounted the broken config fresh and crashed on startup (`ElasticsearchParseException: null-valued setting for node.name`).\n- **Fix applied**: Patched the ConfigMap — `node.name: ${POD_NAME}` (using the existing `POD_NAME` env var) and corrected the seed-host FQDNs to the `elasticsearch` namespace — then deleted the crashing pod so it restarted with the fixed config and rejoined.\n- **Data recovery**: `es-cluster-2`'s fresh PVC had no data, so `app-data`'s primary shard had no valid copy (only a stale one on `es-cluster-0`). Used `_cluster/reroute` with `allocate_stale_primary` (`accept_data_loss: true`) to restore it from the stale copy, then it re-replicated to `es-cluster-2`.\n\nVerified:\n1. `_cluster/health` → `green`, 3/3 nodes.\n2. `_cat/nodes` shows `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, `es-cluster-2`.\n3. `app-data` is searchable and returns its document (`\"msg\": \"seed\"`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1072,"cache_read_input_tokens":99519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1072},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9d35971-1f0c-45a5-8c64-35f97b626f6c","uuid":"6f047f2d-c0b5-4cd6-a8a4-12ce38e037b1","request_id":"req_011CcsSB2rxPcowgroetrDe1"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":254798,"duration_api_ms":196634,"ttft_ms":1668,"ttft_stream_ms":1171,"time_to_request_ms":62,"num_turns":21,"result":"Root cause and fix:\n\n- **Root cause**: The `es-config` ConfigMap had `node.name:` set to a blank value (invalid — ES requires a non-null value) and `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed at the wrong namespace (`.default.svc` instead of `.elasticsearch.svc`). Because it's mounted via `subPath`, already-running pods (`es-cluster-0/1`) kept their original good copy in memory, but `es-cluster-2`'s PVC and pod had been wiped and recreated, so it mounted the broken config fresh and crashed on startup (`ElasticsearchParseException: null-valued setting for node.name`).\n- **Fix applied**: Patched the ConfigMap — `node.name: ${POD_NAME}` (using the existing `POD_NAME` env var) and corrected the seed-host FQDNs to the `elasticsearch` namespace — then deleted the crashing pod so it restarted with the fixed config and rejoined.\n- **Data recovery**: `es-cluster-2`'s fresh PVC had no data, so `app-data`'s primary shard had no valid copy (only a stale one on `es-cluster-0`). Used `_cluster/reroute` with `allocate_stale_primary` (`accept_data_loss: true`) to restore it from the stale copy, then it re-replicated to `es-cluster-2`.\n\nVerified:\n1. `_cluster/health` → `green`, 3/3 nodes.\n2. `_cat/nodes` shows `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, `es-cluster-2`.\n3. `app-data` is searchable and returns its document (`\"msg\": \"seed\"`).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b9d35971-1f0c-45a5-8c64-35f97b626f6c","total_cost_usd":0.9833232,"usage":{"input_tokens":300,"cache_creation_input_tokens":39850,"cache_read_input_tokens":1740544,"output_tokens":14744,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":39850,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_to